    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-02T22:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-02T22:41:00-05:00" n="1590"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1590">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/94.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-02T21:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1914, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This afternoon German consular representative requested assistance of Admiral
                    Mayo and of this office to prevent local authorities from boarding the steamship
                        <hi rend="italic">Antonina</hi> of Hamburg-American line in transit Europe
                    and taking off Mexican accused of homicide. Captain believes that accusation is
                    mere pretext and man is wanted on political charges and refused authorities
                    permission to board ship. Authorities have placed a guard of soldiers on the
                    wharf with artillery and machine guns threaten to sink ship if she attempts to
                    leave the pier. This office has taken no action in the matter and will not
                    unless directed by Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
